## 12. Development Guidance for Engineering Teams

### Engineering Principles
Examples:
- keep modules loosely coupled
- separate business logic from transport layer
- design APIs contract-first
- write migration scripts for schema changes

### Coding Standards Guidance
Examples:
- consistent naming
- layered architecture
- standardized error handling
- test coverage for service logic

### Module Boundaries
Explain what should remain isolated.

### Reuse Guidelines
Examples:
- reuse shared utilities carefully
- avoid central dumping-ground libraries

### Definition of Done (Technical)
Examples:
- feature implemented
- tests added
- API documented
- logs and metrics added
- security checks passed

